{"editorCode":"         \n\t\t;Broken rectangle\n\n;Ebba constructed a broken rectangle and she tries to \"close\" it. She manages to do so by finding a specific relation between the values of the variable a and b. She related these two variables with the solution of a linear system. Can you try it yourself?\n\n;;Click the papyrus button in order to read the instructions and some questions that will help you during your engagement with this activity.\n\n\n\nclean\nrectangle 2 3\n\nto rectangle :a :b\npu setpos [0 -100 0] pd\nfd 230 rt 90 fd 100 rt 90\nfd 30*:a+20*:b rt 90 fd 10*:a+10*:b\nrt 90\npu lt 90 fd 100 pd rt 90\nend\n\nclean\nrectangle 2 3\n\nTO rectangle2 :a :b\npu setpos [0 -100 0] pd  ; moving the avatar\nfd ...\nrt 90 \nfd ...\nrt 90\nfd ... \nrt 90 \nfd ...\nrt 90\npu lt 90 fd 100 pd rt 90  ; moving the avatar \nEND\n\nclean\nrectangle2 2 3\n\n\n\n\n\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"                      ..................................................\n                               BROKEN RECTANGLE\n                      ..................................................\n\n\nRun the command \"rectangle 2 3\". A broken line with two horizontal and two vertical parts is constructed. That is the \"broken rectangle\". \n\nTask 1:\nEnable the variation tool (by clicking on the trace of the avatar) and set the value range for each variable from 0 to 7.\nStarting from the values a=0 and b=0, change one of them and notice the way it affects the sides of the broken rectangle. \nTry to close the broken line into a rectangle and note the values of the variables that caused it. (a=? b=?)\n\nDoes it work for any value that a and b take?\n\nTask 2:\nStudy the procedure \"rectangle\" that created the broken rectangle and try to interpret algebraically your answers at Task 1.  \nWhat is the relation between the variables a and b with the equations:\n30a+20b=230 and 10a+10b=100  ?\n\nTask 3:\nTry to reform the previous procedure and write a new one, the \"rectangle2\" in order to construct the broken line \"unbroken\" (closed) forming a rectangle, when a=2 and b=5.\nWhich equations will the values of a and b be related with? Why?\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}